The paper proposes a loss function for neural networks reconstructing a set of elements without considering order, which is a common problem in machine learning tasks related to sets, such as object reconstruction and rule learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and information theory (cs.IT).
